00%20PAC-3%20MSEs%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20The%20company%20said%20there%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20increase%26quot%3B%20for%202027.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Boeing%20is%20surging%20PAC-3%20missile%20seekers%2C%20critical%20components%20that%20enable%20the%20Patriot%20system%20to%20identify%2C%20track%2C%20and%20intercept%20threats%2C%20and%20Raytheon%2C%20which%20makes%20Patriot%20radars%20and%20launchers%2C%20is%20boosting%20PAC-2%20interceptor%20missile%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20annual%20production%20of%20Patriot%20missiles%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%20somewhere%20around%20850%20to%20880%20per%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fhome%2Fpost%2Fp-167542552%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Fabian%20Hoffman%2C%20an%20air%20defense%20and%20missile%20expert%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Oslo.%20That%20number%20could%20hit%201%2C130%20by%202027.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%2C%20far%20from%20the%20only%20adversarial%20nation%20the%20West%20is%20worried%20about%2C%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%20producing%20roughly%20840%20to%201%2C020%20of%20its%209M723%20Iskander%20short-range%20ballistic%20missiles%20and%20the%20air-launched%20Kh-47M2%20Kinzhal%20short-%20to%20medium-range%20ballistic%20missiles%20a%20year.%20Those%20weapons%20are%20only%20two%20missiles%20in%20a%20vast%20arsenal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20imbalance%20leaves%20the%20West%20with%20a%20concerning%20math%20problem.%20Air%20defenders%20tend%20to%20need%20to%20fire%20two%20or%20three%20interceptors%20to%20reliably%20take%20out%20one%20incoming%20threat%2C%20making%20things%20even%20more%20complicated.%20Patriot%20isn't%20the%20only%20air%20defense%20game%20in%20town%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20key%20capability%20that%20could%20be%20stressed%20without%20deep%20stockpiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrian%20Kubik%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20PAC-3%20programs%20at%20Lockheed%20Martin%20Missiles%20and%20Fire%20Control%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3BLockheed%20Martin%20recognizes%20the%20critical%20need%20for%20PAC-3%20MSE%2C%20and%20we're%20working%20closely%20with%20the%20US%20Army%20and%20suppliers%20to%20increase%20our%20production%20rate%20to%20meet%20the%20worldwide%20demand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20robust%20infrastructure%20and%20supply%20chain%20provide%20a%20strong%20foundation%20for%20increasing%20production%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20company%20is%20%26quot%3Btaking%20proactive%20steps%20and%20making%20internal%20investments%20to%20help%20support%20our%20suppliers%2C%20accelerate%20delivery%2C%20and%20decrease%20production%20roadblocks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERaytheon%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Bit's%20more%20important%20than%20ever%20to%20co-produce%2C%20co-develop%2C%20and%20collaborate%20to%20get%20the%20best%20capabilities%20to%20the%20field%20quickly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20it%20has%20entered%20into%20new%20partnerships%20to%20increase%20production%2C%20is%20increasing%20its%20staff%2C%20and%20has%20also%20committed%20nearly%20%241B%20to%20secure%20critical%20materials%20from%20suppliers%20and%20ramp%20manufacturing%20for%20Patriot%20radars.%20The%20company%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bby%20the%20end%20of%202025%2C%20Raytheon%2C%20along%20with%20our%20suppliers%2C%20will%20accelerate%20delivery%20times%20for%20Patriot%20radars%20by%2025%25.%26quot%3B%20Patriot%20GEM-T%20interceptor%20production%20will%20increase%20by%20150%25%20by%202028%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22patriot%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F579a3c2a88e4a7dd488ba960%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221363%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Patriot%20Air%20and%20Missile%20Defense%20launcher%20fires%20an%20interceptor%20during%20a%20previous%20test%20at%20White%20Sands%20Missile%20Range%20in%20New%20Mexico.%20The%20latest%20configuration%20of%20the%20system%2C%20called%20PDB-8%2C%20has%20passed%20four%20flight%20tests%20and%20is%20now%20with%20the%20U.S.%20Army%20for%20a%20final%20evaluation.%3Cp%3ERaytheon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHoffman%20cautioned%20that%20even%20if%20the%20West's%20production%20of%20missile%20interceptors%2C%20like%20the%20Patriots%2C%20exceeds%20Russian%20conventional%20ballistic%20missile%20production%2C%20%26quot%3Bthis%20will%20not%20solve%20Europe's%20problems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20for%20the%20US%2C%20the%20threat%20isn't%20Russia%20alone.%20The%20Pentagon%20is%20eyeing%20China's%20growing%20ballistic%20missile%20arsenal%20and%20recognizing%20that%20it%20is%20going%20to%20need%20substantial%20air%20defenses.%20American%20allies%20in%20the%20Pacific%20realize%20that%2C%20too.%20And%20foes%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20can't%20be%20dismissed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatriots%20are%20used%20by%20European%20allies%2C%20as%20well%20as%20allies%20and%20partner%20nations%20in%20Asia%20and%20the%20Middle%20East.%20There%20are%2019%20operators%20worldwide%2C%20and%20that%20means%20a%20lot%20of%20competing%20demand%2C%20especially%20with%20some%20nations%20at%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20West's%20increased%20production%20is%20starting%20at%20a%20time%20when%20interceptor%20stockpiles%20appear%20to%20be%20running%20low%20in%20the%20West%2C%20putting%20extra%20pressure%20on%20production%20efforts.%20The%20challenge%20in%20fixing%20the%20problem%20is%20that%20the%20Patriot%20missiles%20and%20batteries%20take%20time%20to%20make%2C%20and%20in%20that%20time%2C%20immediate%20demands%20compete%20heavily%20with%20stockpiling%20needs%20for%20future%20fights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThomas%20Laliberty%2C%20Raytheon's%20president%20of%20land%20and%20air%20defense%20systems%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Fus-patriot-defeat-europe-sampt-air-defense-volodymyr-zelenskyy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%20that%20%26quot%3Bit%20takes%20us%2012%20months%20to%20build%20a%20Patriot%20radar%2C%20but%20it%20takes%20us%2024%20months%20to%20get%20all%20the%20parts.%26quot%3B%20Meeting%20global%20demand%20often%20means%20pulling%20from%20existing%20stockpiles%2C%20for%20both%20launchers%20and%20missiles%20alike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2211de6078-b2ec-4f68-b796-e0d35d365dd4%5C%22%3EStrained%20stockpiles%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon%20rejected%20a%20report%20from%20The%20Guardian%20last%20month%20that%20said%20that%20the%20US%20only%20has%20about%2025%25%20of%20the%20Patriot%20interceptors%20it%20needs.%20Pentagon%20spokesperson%20Lt.%20Col.%20Bryon%20McGarry%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20US%20military%20has%20what%20it%20needs%20to%20fight%20and%20win%20any%20mission%2C%20anywhere%2C%20anytime.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20standing%20in%20front%20of%20a%20Patriot%20anti-aircraft%20missile%20system%20during%20his%20visit%20to%20a%20military%20training%20area%20in%20Germany%20on%20June%2011%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666a59b5764df1611259519d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20standing%20in%20front%20of%20a%20Patriot%20anti-aircraft%20missile%20system%20during%20his%20visit%20to%20a%20military%20training%20area%20in%20Germany%20on%20June%2011%2C%202024.%3Cp%3EJens%20B%C3%BCttner%2FPool%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20beginning%20of%20last%20month%2C%20however%2C%20the%20Pentagon%20abruptly%20paused%20weapons%20shipments%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20including%20Patriot%20interceptors%2C%20amid%20concerns%20about%20US%20weapons%20stockpiles.%20The%20move%20was%20reportedly%20triggered%20by%20Elbridge%20Colby%2C%20the%20undersecretary%20of%20defense%20for%20policy%20and%20someone%20who%20has%20long%20been%20deeply%20vocal%20about%20insufficient%20US%20readiness%20for%20war%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20reversed%20the%20decision%20on%20military%20aid%20but%20changed%20how%20weapons%20are%20being%20provided%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20putting%20cost%20and%20stockpile%20burdens%20on%20European%20allies%20while%20the%20US%20handles%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20that%20back-and-forth%2C%20the%20president%20commented%20on%20the%20Patriots%20during%20a%20press%20conference%2C%20telling%20a%20Ukrainian%20journalist%20that%20while%20the%20US%20might%20be%20able%20to%20get%20additional%20systems%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Cspan%3Ethey're%20very%20hard%20to%20get.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20them%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20in%20late%20June.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20Pentagon%20rejected%20assertions%20that%20there%20is%20a%20problem%2C%20US%20officials%20have%20previously%20suggested%20that%20there%20is%20at%20least%20strain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%20Adm.%20Samuel%20Paparo%2C%20the%20head%20of%20US%20Indo-Pacific%20Command%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twz.com%2Fair%2Fconflicts-eating-into-critical-munitions-stockpiles-needed-for-china-fight-top-u-s-officer-in-pacific-warns%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%20that%20the%20fighting%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20Ukraine%20was%20eating%20into%20the%20US%20stockpile%2C%20pulling%20assets%20away%20that%20would%20be%20needed%20in%20a%20fight%20in%20his%20priority%20theater.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20admiral%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bto%20say%20otherwise%20would%20be%20dishonest.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen.%20James%20Mingus%2C%20the%20vice%20chief%20of%20staff%20of%20the%20Army%2C%20said%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20US%20Patriot%20battalions%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20very%20stressed%20force%20element.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Shank%2C%20a%20retired%20Army%20colonel%20and%20the%20former%20commandant%20of%20the%20Army%20Air%20Defense%20Artillery%20School%20at%20Fort%20Sill%2C%20Oklahoma%2C%20shared%20with%20The%20War%20Zone%20that%20the%20US%20was%20short%20on%20Patriot%20interceptors%20even%20in%202021%2C%20before%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20war%2C%20he%20explained%2C%20has%20exacerbated%20longstanding%20problems%20with%20missile%20stockpiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20clear%20effort%20underway%20to%20expand%20US%20Army%20stocks%20as%20the%20service%20aims%20to%20quadruple%20its%20purchase%20of%20interceptors%2C%20from%203%2C376%20to%2013%2C773%2C%20with%20a%20substantial%20%241.3%20billion%20investment%20in%20Patriot%20missiles%2C%20a%20move%20that%20reflects%20repeated%20calls%20from%20experts%20and%20officials%20for%20far%20deeper%20magazines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2232573dab-2ab8-47d3-8fa5-d77a51b42402%5C%22%3EWhat%20conflicts%20are%20showing%20about%20the%20need%20for%20air%20defenses%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20conflicts%2C%20specifically%20the%20massive%20missile%20and%20drone%20attacks%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20are%20driving%20the%20new%20demand%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhuge-air-battles-show-us-needs-most-missile-war-china-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eshowing%20how%20critical%20air%20defenses%20are%20in%20modern%20warfare%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222058%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20military%20personnel%20display%20a%20downed%20Russian%20drone%20during%20a%20press%20conference.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654f69c236d588dc55cf0207%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20military%20personnel%20display%20a%20downed%20Russian%20drone%20during%20a%20press%20conference.%3Cp%3ESERGEI%20SUPINSKY%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C