ion%20method%20since%20natural%20pollination%20was%20not%20effective.%20This%20method%2C%20involving%20the%20delicate%20brushing%20of%20each%20petal%2C%20consumed%20a%20lot%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20experimented%20on%20several%20plants.%20Nothing%20worked%20for%20the%20first%20three%20to%20four%20years.%20One%20evening%2C%20I%20noticed%20flower%20buds%20and%20hoped%20they%20would%20turn%20into%20fruit.%20About%20seven%20to%20eight%20months%20later%2C%20I%20was%20overjoyed%20to%20see%20my%20efforts%20bear%20fruit.%20I%20haven%E2%80%99t%20named%20the%20variety%20yet.%20As%20long%20as%20it%20gives%20me%20a%20good%20yield%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20happy%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%2070-year-old%20farmer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECross-pollination%20vs%20natural%20pollination%3A%20Expert%20insights%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Nitai%20Mudi%2C%20Senior%20Scientist%20at%20Krishi%20Vigyan%20Kendra%20(Agriculture%20Science%20Centre)%2C%20explains%2C%20%E2%80%9CCross-pollination%20is%20a%20common%20practice.%20However%2C%20hybrid%20varieties%20often%20don%E2%80%99t%20produce%20viable%20seeds%20for%20future%20use.%20The%20best%20results%20often%20come%20from%20natural%20pollination.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20District%20Horticulture%20Officer%2C%20requesting%20anonymity%20due%20to%20protocol%2C%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20horticulture%20department%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20conduct%20fruit%20variety%20identification.%20That%20can%20only%20be%20done%20through%20gene%20testing%20or%20tissue%20culture%20at%20specialised%20labs%20like%20Bidhan%20Chandra%20Krishi%20Viswavidyalaya%20in%20Kalyani.%20But%20most%20farmers%20avoid%20this%20due%20to%20high%20costs%20and%20are%20content%20with%20a%20good%20harvest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20fruitful%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20nearly%20a%20decade%2C%20Halder%20focused%20on%20preserving%20this%20resilient%20breed.%20To%20scale%20up%2C%20he%20bo